@node Disclaimer
Although this collection of games is proven to be stable in everyday use,
there may be bugs which I haven't spotted (very unlikely, in about 2K of
code...).  I do not, will not and can not accept any responsibility
whatsoever for damage to equipment, loss of data etc.  This collection of
programs is provided "as-is", with no warranty of any kind, either expressed
or implied.  All use is at your own risk.

Unsatisfactory Software have absolutely no connection with Daz or the Daz
Doorstep Challenge whatsoever. We do not endorse or condone their products.
This collection of games is not designed to advertise Daz or any rival
brands, but merely to take the piss out of Shane Ritchie and the Daz
Doorstep Challenge.
@endnode

@node Inst "Installation"
I couldn't be bothered to write an installation script, so just dump it all
in one (rather small) directory.  Move hisoftbasic.library to libs: if you
haven't got it already.
@endnode

@node Req "Requirements"
Daz-Chaz 2: hisoftbasic.library
Daz-Chaz 3: ARexx
@endnode

@node DC1 "Daz-Chaz: the Daz Doorstep Challenge Game"
@{u}DAZ-CHAZ: The Daz Doorstep Challenge Game@{uu}
@{i}Written by Chris Young of Unsatisfactory Software 1996@{ui}

Have you ever wanted to take part in the "Daz Doorstep Challenge", as seen
so many times on the TV ads?  This program will allow you to do just that.

Select the variety of washing powder you normally use from the menu, and
read the result.

I hope you are successful.  I do, really.

Controls: Select washing powder with numeric keys 1-4 and ENTER
@endnode

@node DC2 "Daz-Chaz 2: The Ultimate (Daz Doorstep) Challenge"
@{u}DAZ-CHAZ 2: The Ultimate (Daz Doorstep) Challenge@{uu}
@{i}Written by Chris Young (again)@{ui}

Will @{i}your@{ui} whites pass the Daz Doorstep Challenge?

Just select the colour your whites are (after being washed, of course), and
read whether you are successful or not.

Controls: Use left mouse button to "open door" and select colour.  The
close gadget quits, of course.
On the title screen, the space bar toggles whether you are using
Pre-Workbench 2.0 colours (Blue-White-Black-Orange) or Workbench 2.0
colours (Grey-Black-White-Blue).  This selects the right setting (assuming
you have not changed the default palette) automatically through the
Workbench environment variable.  This is normally set in the
startup-sequence upon booting, but if it isn't the program will not run.
Set it from a CLI/Shell with...

SETENV WORKBENCH <workbench version number>

Where <workbench version number> is your workbench version number.  NOT THE
RELEASE NUMBER.

You can find the Workbench version number by typing:

VERSION

For example, for Workbench 2.0 the number might be 37.67
@endnode

@node DC3 "Daz-Chaz III: Advanced Washing Powder Simulator"
@{u}Daz-Chaz III: Advanced Washing Powder Simulator@{uu}
@{i}By Chris Young 1998@{ui}

The best one yet!  Buy some washing powder, then wash some whites with it. 
Will they come out white or, erm, not?  Will Shane lie to the millions of
viewers at home, simply to make Daz look good?  Play this and find out!

Unsatisfactory Software would like to point out that we don't really think
Shane lies about how good Daz is, and that the Daz Doorstep Challenge really
is filmed live.  We are not connected with Daz in any way, either.
@endnode

@node CasioDAZ1 "Daz-Chaz for Casio fx-7300G"
@{u}DAZ-CHAZ: The Daz Doorstep Challenge Game@{uu}
@{i}Program by Chris Young of Unsatisfactory Software 1996@{ui}
Stuart Flint was moaning (about me stealing his ideas, which I didn't do),
but I suppose he may have given some ideas (well, one).
Oh, and Phillip Lake just agreed (and then wrote his own version)

This is approximately 127.1274657651421 bytes long, and / means "triangle"
<> is supposed to be an equals sign with a line through it (in prgm-rel)

" "
"DAZ  DOORSTEP":"  CHALLENGE"
" "/
"WHICH WASHINGPOWDER?"
"1 DAZ"
"2 PERSIL"
"3 ASDA"
? -> Z
Z<>1 => "YOU FAILED!"
Z=1 => "YOU PASSED!"

@{"More calc games!" link Contact}
@endnode

@node CasioDAZ2 "Daz Challenge"
@{u}Daz Challenge@{uu}
@{i}Program by Phillip Lake of Unsatisfactory Software 1996@{ui}

Select one of the hidden boxes of washing powder, if it's Daz, then you
have passed the Daz Doorstep Challenge.

Controls: Select washing powder with keys 1-3, and EXE

"DAZ DOORSTEP CHALLENGE"
"WHICH WASHINGPOWDER 1,2,3"
? -> Z
Int (Ran#×3)+1 -> Y
Z=Y => "WELL DONE!    YOU HAVE     PASSED THE   DAZ DOORSTEP CHALLENGE"
Z <> Y => "YOU HAVE NOT PASSED THE   DAZ DOORSTEP CHALLENGE"

@{"More calc games!" link Contact}
@endnode

